  "title": "Core Concepts of Foundations of Getting Started with AWS",
  "lessonText": "Understanding the core concepts of AWS is essential for beginners to navigate the cloud effectively.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- **Cloud Computing**: Delivery of computing services over the internet.\n- **AWS Services**: A wide range of services including computing power, storage, and databases.\n- **Regions and Availability Zones**: Geographical areas that provide redundancy and reliability.\n- **Elasticity and Scalability**: Ability to scale resources up or down based on demand.\n- **Security and Compliance**: AWS provides tools to help secure your data and comply with regulations.\n- **Billing and Pricing**: Understanding the pay-as-you-go model and cost management tools."
  }
}
